Q.vnet peering?
â” Consider there are 2 vnets
â” 1 from san francisco and 1 from india
â” 2 vnets having diff range of ip where subnetting principle comes
â” Default vnet ip range -same ,so diff range needed for both vnet to possible
â” Soo if we need to connect the vnet ,s without using internet we can do vnet peering b/w the vnet
â” After vnet peering the machines from the both vnet can talk using private ip
Q. bastion host helps to communicate using private ip within the vnet.how?
â” Vm inside the Vnet can communicate without the internet.
â” Bastion Host sits inside your VNet.
â” You connect to Bastion through the Azure portal.
â” Bastion then connects to your VM using its private IP, without needing internet or a public IP.
â” So, Bastion acts like a secure door to reach your VMs inside the private network.
Note:
You connect to the Bastion Host through Azure Portal using HTTPS (port 443).From
the Bastion Host, it initiates RDP/SSH connection to the target VM using its private IP address.
