Q. Key Characteristics of Azure Cloud Data Centers?
â” Security: Strict physical & logical security controls to protect your data.
â” Connectivity:
â—† Private IP-based for secure VM-to-VM communication within Azure.
â—† VNet Peering to connect VNets across regions securely.
â—† NAT Gateways to access the internet without exposing private IPs.
â—† VNet Endpoints to access Azure services like Azure Files privately with low latency.
â” Note on Public IPs:2 Azure VMs communicating using public IPs won't use Azureâ€™s internal
network = slower.
â” Resource Groups:
â—† - Logical container to manage resources like VMs, disks, IPs, etc.
â—† - RG can be in one region, but resources inside can be in any region.
â—† - Azure allows nesting groups (group inside group).
â—† - Stores metadata about resources
