Q. powershell commands:
â” Connect-AzAccount # Logs into your Azure account (interactive login)
â” Connect-AzAccount -UseDeviceAuthentication # Logs into Azure using device authentication
(usually for secure login on new devices)
â” get-AzContext # Gets the context of your current Azure session (subscription,
account, and other settings)
â” set-AzContext -Subscription "<subscription-id>" # Sets the current Azure subscription context to
the specified subscription ID
â” get-AzSubscription # Lists all Azure subscriptions available for the current account
â” get-AzResourceGroup # Lists all Azure resource groups under the current
