Q. What are Managed Identities in Azure?
â” Managed Identities are identities provided by Azure Active Directory (azure AD)
â” allow Azure services to authenticate to each other without the need for credentials
â” managed identities belongs to groups
â” managed identities work within scope of azure
â” Credentials: password and secret(stored in code)
â” Credentials are automatically managed by azure
â” We dont want to handle
â” Need to give permissions to managed identities
â” Two types of managed identities:
â—† System-Assigned Managed Identity:
â— Created automatically when you enable managed identity for a resource like
a virtual machine (VM), app service, or function.
â— if the resource is deleted, the identity is also deleted.
â— The identity is used only by that specific resource.
â—† User-Assigned Managed Identity:
â— We need to create it
â— Created separately from any resource and can be assigned to one or more
resources.
â— it stays around until you manually delete it.
â— Used across multiple resources
