Q. azure functions:
Azure Functions is the code that you write and run in response to events or triggers.
â” Pay Only for What You Use:
â” Integrated Security:
â—† Azure Functions can be secured with built-in authentication and authorization
options.
â—† You can use HTTP triggers to accept GET, POST, or other types of HTTP
requests, ensuring that your functions can be securely accessed over the web.
â” Create Microservices and Simple APIs:
â—† You can use Azure Functions to create microservices or lightweight APIs that
can handle specific tasks, such as processing events or serving HTTP requests.
â” Run Azure Functions on Various Events:
â—† Time based triggers
