Q. iaac have 3 tools:
1. Infrastructure provisioning tools
2. Configuration management tools:
3. Server templating tools:
Infrastructure provisioning tools:
â” Terraform â€“ multicloud
â” Boto in aws
â” Cloud formation in aws
â” Azure biceps
â” Azure ARM template(json format)
â” Adv: if its is supported in azure its possible
â” maynot be 100 % for biceps and terraform
â” It may delete and recreate, some times it shutdown
â” In Azure -> delete and recreate-> because resizing isn't always supported dynamically
â” No guarantee that Changes Will Just Modify because Cloud providers handle resources
differently.(aws and azure), Provisioning tools follow cloud provider rules. so they sometimes
destroy and recreate resources.
â” Most of time when u provision it bring up a new instance
Configuration management tools:
â” Used for upgrading and modifying infrastructure configurations
â” Manual: people do in diff ways,cannot guarantee the consistency and when error occurs they fix
it by their own ways-> delta grows
â” At some point of time some code will not work on a particular machine. Need to fix without
accessing that machine. Give one command and execute it (before they validate and execute).
One by one doing without actualy having access to production is not good idea. So I can use
same script and create new machine. Here high chance of configuration dripped/snow flakes.
â” Ansible
â—† Git went from 0 to 95 when devops comes
â—† install ansible on centralized server and connect to the production server.
â—† Connection done using ssh ,internally uses scp(Send configuration files to servers
using scp.),
â—† Ansible works on push pull model: gather the facts and push(configuration changes
always push based)
â—† No agent required on push model
â—† Push: Ansible collects facts from a central server and pushes configurations to target
machines via SSH.,No agent
â—† Pull model: Each server (agent) pulls its configuration from a central server and
applies it.
â— Agents should be installed
â— if agent is there -possiblity of security attack
â— problem: push things to production server
â— in puppet and chef - unless u trigger it wont push
â— o Works even if the central server is down temporarily.
â— o Requires agents to be installed on every server.
â— Fact collection is pull model(agent will come and pull and install)
Pull models:
â” Chef
â” Puppet
â” in puppet and chef - unless u trigger it wont push
Server templating tools: Server templating tools help create pre-configured environments so you can
quickly set up and manage servers without manual setup.
â” o Vagrant (help to create vm)
â” o Docker (create containers)
