Q. require_provider:Minor version,Major version and patch?
â” ~> = minor version that can be upgraded
â” > inside â€œ â€
â” 2.0 means it will go to latest version of 2
â” 2.40.0 = major version,minor version and patch
â” Patch =fixing bugs
â—† Schedule for releasing patch
â” Minor versions= within the generics
â—† they improves performance,
â—† adding to existing significant changes
â” Major versions= java version
â—† (1.7 =they added generics,1.8=lambda (pass around functions),
â—† so these are big changes.
â—† Introduced a lot of features and improved speed.
â” Hot fixes - within 24 hrs
â—† Immediately release
