Q. Multiple vmâ€™s creation in terraform?
Q. storage account?
â” Blobs- Binary large Objects(managed by containers)- to store large files
â—† Binary storage is block storage,possible some block is
underutilized,access-fast
â” File share
â” Tables(NOSQL Date)- used for storing huge data
â—† Partition key-you have multiple machines,based on which key ur data is
partitioned,
â— stored on diff partitions or nodes
â—† Row key - Within the same machine
â—† If u r searching is based on partition key and row key -> very fast
â—† Because the data is index spaced on these 2
â—† Index: like an index of the book
â—† Which tells u where u can find the dataâ€™
â—† Data stored as pages in db
â—† Data stored based on rows in pages
â—† When u r querying the db go to index
â—† Very fast
â—† Wide Column based db?
â— Store data based on columns and not rows
â— If we only want to retrieve the things of 2 specific column(phn
number,aadhaar number)
â— So we can store many phone number and aadhar in 1 page
â— Soo time reduced
â— Read time reduced
â” Queues:
â” Here synchronous and asynchronous communication comes
â” In synchronous- load balancer - helps to route ur req to one of the instance
â—† Sent a msg
â—† Wait for response
â” Asynchronous - no load balancer
â—† Always a broker in it
â—† broker(kafka,rabbit and queue)
â—† Senter is not waiting
â” 2 types of asynchronous - queue mode and publish subscribe model
â” Queue -client will come and pick the req
â—† No need a load balancer
â—† One of the instance of client pick the msg
â” Public subscribe-
â” Broker will notify immediately
â” All services can intimate using broker so no load balancer needed
â” Microservices:
â—† Load balancer -2 types
â— Path based routing
â— Distribute load
â—† Authentication(valid user/not) and authorization(can you do the thing/not)
â—† How do u manage authorization-RBAC
â—† When u create user
â—† Front end application - data maintained in cache -y - scalability -cant
scale-externalize the data(redis,memcache)
